Class AnagramCheckerApplication

  • java.lang.Object
    • anagrams.AnagramCheckerApplication

    • Field Detail

      • previousResults

        public static Map<String,​Result> previousResults
        Global TreeMap collection to store previous user results from the external file in a cache. Key is a String representing the username and value is an object representing the words used in the program, the result and the username.

      • displayWelcomeMessage

        public static void displayWelcomeMessage()
        Displays welcome message to the user at the beginning of the program.

      • captureUserInput

        public static String[] captureUserInput()
        Captures and returns as a String[] the user input from the console. Validation rules in place to ensure that invalid input from the user is caught.
        Returns:
        String[] containing user input

      • processUserInput

        public static void processUserInput​(String[] userInput)
        Processes the user input from the console. If the words have been processed before they will not be added to the cache or written to the file but the result will be displayed. If the words are new they will be stored in the external file and the cache.
        Parameters:
        userInput - input from the user containing username and the words to be checked

      • writeNewResultToExternalFile

        public static void writeNewResultToExternalFile​(String username,
                                                String word1,
                                                String word2,
                                                boolean anagramResult)
        Writes to an external file the results of a new set of words being processed by the anagram checker. Also writes to file the date and time of the result being processed.
        Parameters:
        username - the username
        word1 - the first word used in th program
        word2 - the second word used in th program
        anagramResult - the result of the anagram checker

      • areAnagrams

        public static boolean areAnagrams​(String userInput1,
                                  String userInput2)
        Takes two String inputs, checks if they are anagrams of each other and returns the result as a boolean.
        Parameters:
        userInput1 - first word to be checked
        userInput2 - second word to be checked
        Returns:
        boolean result of the check

      • displayMenu

        public static void displayMenu()
        Prints to the console the options that a user can choose from and makes appropriate method calls according to their choice. Includes validation to ensure invalid input is caught.

      • readInPreviousResultsFromFile

        public static void readInPreviousResultsFromFile()
        Reads in any previously processed results from the external file and uses these to populate the cache (Global TreeMap previousResults).

      • haveWordsBeenProcessedBefore

        public static boolean haveWordsBeenProcessedBefore​(String[] userInput)
        Checks the cache (Global TreeMap previousResults) against the user input to see if the words have been processed before or not. Informs the user if they have been processed and returns a boolean true or false depending on the outcome.
        Parameters:
        userInput - user input containing the words to check against the cache of previous results
        Returns:
        boolean true or false depending on the outcome
